Rating: 4
I brought these little gems to a party on Saturday, and literally had people fighting over them! And one lady 'hid' one so she could take it home and have it with coffe in the morning! LOL I made a batch the next day and tested several cakes for doneness - one tester will come out clean, and another will be gooey. My baking time was 5-7 minutes longer and I left them in the tins for another 10 mins. Very chocolatey and moist. The hint of rum and the texture of the coconut are magnificent! And I agree with the light sprinkle of powdered sugar to finish them.

