Lovely little cakes!! Great deep chocolate flavor, the rum adds a nice note. I agree with the thought of doubling the recipe, since it doesn't make a very large batch and a little sprikle of confectioners sugar adds a nice touch.

Rating: 4
My husband and I spent a week on Grand Cayman in January. While there we enjoyed a variety of rum cakes. Upon return, he asked if I couldn't make something similar. I went to Epicurious and typed in rum cake and a few other choices. I found this recipe. Since then I have made it numerous times. It has beome my husband's new favorite! It is quick and easy and delicious. The only thing I changed is to poke the cakes with a tooth pick several times and then drizzle with about 2 teaspoons more rum. Yum! PS I'd love to visit with any other cooks from Albuquerque.

Rating: 2
This cake is not inedible, but you can definitely find a better recipe. The taste was good, but the texture was awful. Very moist, but too dense, like I didn't bake it long enough. When I took it out of the oven, it was done by all accounts -- clean cake tester, firm top, pulled away from sides of pan (I made an 8" round cake). It's really more a brownie than a cake. I think it needs less fat and a leavnening agent.

Rating: 4
